  "page": "Sack of Qohor",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table style=\"margin: 4px 10%; border: 1px solid #aaa; background:#fbfbfb;\"><tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"padding: 2px 0 2px 0.5em;border-left: 10px solid #1e90ff;\">\n<div style=\"width: 50px;\"><img alt=\"Mbox notice.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/40px-Mbox_notice.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/60px-Mbox_notice.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/80px-Mbox_notice.png 2x\" />\n</div></td><td style=\"border: none; padding: 0.25em 0.9em; width: 100%;\"> <b>Note:</b> The title of this article is conjecture and may be subject to change.</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;background: #B0C4DE; text-align:center;\">Sack of Qohor</th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Place</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Qohor\" title=\"Qohor\">Qohor</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Result</th><td>\nGolden Company victory</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<table style=\"width:100%; text-align:left;\">\n<tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #B0C4DE; text-align: center;\"><b>Combatants</b></td></tr><tr><td width=\"50%\" style=\"border-right:1px dotted #aaa;\">Qohor</td>\n    <td width=\"50%\"><a href=\"/index.php/Golden_Company\" title=\"Golden Company\">Golden Company</a></td></tr>\n</tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>A <b>sack of Qohor</b> took place early in the history of the <a href=\"/index.php/Golden_Company\" title=\"Golden Company\">Golden Company</a>. The company took to sack the <a href=\"/index.php/Free_Cities\" title=\"Free Cities\">Free City</a> after the <a href=\"/index.php/Qohor\" title=\"Qohor\">Qohorik</a> leadership refused to honor a contract. This event helped the Golden Company to quickly establish its reputation of never breaking a contract.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rawoiafaegor_rivers.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rawoiafaegor_rivers.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Sack_of_Qohor&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rawoiafaegor_rivers.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rawoiafaegor_rivers.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_World_of_Ice_and_Fire\" title=\"A World of Ice and Fire\">George R. R. Martin's A World of Ice and Fire</a></i>, Aegor Rivers.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260404194045\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.079 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.314 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 220/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 9322/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 4238/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 318/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 557/5000000 bytes\nLua time usage: 0.220/7.000 seconds\nLua virtual size: 5.16 MB/50 MB\nLua estimated memory usage: 0 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%  302.998      1 -total\n 95.92%  290.623      1 Template:Battlebox\n 95.33%  288.849      1 Template:Infobox\n  2.30%    6.982      1 Template:Ref\n  1.45%    4.